AXIOM — An AI-Native Language for Self-Evolving Intelligence

Author:       Antonio Roberts
Created:      2026
Project:      AXIOM Phase 1 — Self-Improving Prompt Agent
Repository:   i:\vsCode\promt-agent

Description:
  AXIOM is a language and agent architecture for building self-improving AI
  systems. Agents are defined by .axiom files — a structured plaintext DSL
  that the system can read, execute, evaluate, and rewrite autonomously.
  The Rewriter agent mutates agent definitions on disk, enabling the language
  to evolve itself over successive runs.

Components authored by Antonio Roberts:
  - AXIOM DSL v0 specification and .axiom file format
  - axiom/ — core engine (client, store, rubric, evolution loop, meta-evolution)
  - axiom/agents/ — Worker, Evaluator, Rewriter, BaseAgent
  - axiom_files/ — DSL agent definitions and parser
  - ui.py — Streamlit browser interface
  - run_axiom.py — DSL language test runner
  - main.py — CLI runner

Third-party dependencies are subject to their own licenses:
  - openai — MIT License
  - streamlit — Apache 2.0 License
  - python-dotenv — BSD License
  - rich — MIT License
  - typer — MIT License
